    • createRule

      public MetricsRule createRule​(java.lang.String name, int locVal, boolean locComp, boolean locCyclo, int cycloVal, boolean cycloComp, int aftdVal, boolean aftdComp, boolean aftdLaa, double laaVal, boolean laaComp) throws java.io.IOException
      Creates a metric rule and saves it in the save file
      Parameters:
      name - The rule name
      locVal - The rule's LOC Value
      locComp - The rule's LOC comparison method: true for greater than, false for lesser than
      locCyclo - The rule's LOC and CYCLO logic operation type: true for And, false for OR
      cycloVal - The rule's CYCLO Value
      cycloComp - The rule's CYCLO comparison method: true for greater than, false for lesser than
      aftdVal - The rule's AFTD Value
      aftdComp - The rule's AFTD comparison method: true for greater than, false for lesser than
      aftdLaa - The rule's AFTD and LAA logic operation type: true for And, false for OR
      laaVal - The rule's LAA Value
      laaComp - The rule's LAA comparison method: true for greater than, false for lesser than
      Returns:
      Returns the created rule After saving it to the save file
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - Throws this exception case the are errors writing the save file(EX: file is missing);

    • MetricLongMethod

      public void MetricLongMethod​(boolean and, boolean locLessThan, boolean cycloLessThan, int locGUI, int cycloGUI)
      sets column MetricLongMethod true or false, depending on inputs in GUI and comparing those inputs with values from file
      Parameters:
      and - boolean that comes from GUI deciding AND/OR operator (true=AND/false=OR) between loc and cyclo
      locLessThan - boolean: if true then use ( locFile <= locGUI ) for comparison; else ( locFile > locGUI )
      cycloLessThan - boolean: if true then use ( cycloFile <= cycloGUI ) for comparison; else ( cycloFile > cycloGUI )
      locGUI - loc value input from GUI
      cycloGUI - cyclo value input from GUI

    • MetricFeatureEnvy

      public void MetricFeatureEnvy​(boolean and, boolean atfdLessThan, boolean laaLessThan, int atfdGUI, double laaGUI)
      sets column MetricFeatureEnvy true or false, depending on inputs in GUI and comparing those inputs with values from file
      Parameters:
      and - boolean that comes from GUI deciding AND/OR operator (true=AND/false=OR) between atfd and laa
      atfdLessThan - boolean: if true then use ( atfdFile <= atfdGUI ) for comparison; else ( atfdFile > atfdGUI )
      laaLessThan - boolean: if true then use ( laaFile <= laaGUI ) for comparison; else ( laaFile > laaGUI )
      atfdGUI - atfd value input from GUI
      laaGUI - laa value input from GUI
